ČIn Memory of Trevor John Antill ACIB
1937-2010
Trevor was the Creator and Founder of The Monarch's Way Long Distance Footpath which follows the
escape route taken by King Charles II after his defeat at the battle of Worcester. The 615 mile
footpath starts in Worcester and continues to Stratford-upon-Avon, Charmouth and then to Shoreham.
Donations from The Monarch's Way Association, family and friends paid for this memorial bench."┐
